2000-12-12  Bruno Haible  <haible@clisp.cons.org>

        * Makefile.in: Use $(MAKE) instead of $(MAKE) -r. Needed with Solaris
          "make", which doesn't set MAKE as expected by @SET_MAKE@ if -r is
          given. Reported by Toshimitsu Fujiwara.

